403, 405 Bleecker Street (originally George Street), at and adjoining the N.E. corner of 11th Street (originally Hammond Street). The corner building contains a former saloon, being remodelled. The name George Street applied only to the uppermost section of Bleecker, north of Christopher Street, and was lost around 1829. The name Hammond Street was applied to this cross street west of Seventh Avenue, and was retained till about 1870. See 11th Street. March 8, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

11th Street (formerly Hammond Street), at and adjoining the S.W. corner of Bleecker Street, showing 286 to about 270 West 11th Street.
Bleecker Street is another old Village street which, like 4th Street, has long ago taken the name of an East Side cross-street of which it happened to form a continuation.
May 20, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

West 11th Street, south side and east of Bleekker Street.
P. L. Sperr
May 12, 1940
